@everyone it's time! Please head over to https://snapshot.org/#/echelonassembly.eth to cast your votes. Voting closes Friday, March 24 at noon EST.

**Emissary Prime Election 2023**: https://snapshot.org/#/echelonassembly.eth/proposal/0x742166884c287f1f12feacc03bd2a9a6b1c97bfdfeb0afeddd2c7809799a129c

**PRIME Recapture**: https://snapshot.org/#/echelonassembly.eth/proposal/0xcf1ebeb8378bfcd92345b533bb35b4a3216260eade8d5368330da280598d8718

All wallets holding PRIME or caching PKs at 11:59pm EST on March 15 are eligible to vote. To ensure full participation, we have removed the EADA (ex. Parallel card) requirement for voting eligibility. Our wallet analysis found that less than 1% of wallets were suspicious. In addition, roughly two thirds of wallets holding PRIME did not hold an EADA. When voting closes, Echelon will review and audit participating wallets to validate results over 72 hours. During this time, any wallet involved in gaming quadratic votes will be blocklisted and disqualified.

Update on community votes @everyone.

149,450 is the number of circulating weighted votes for the PRIME Recapture vote: https://snapshot.org/#/echelonassembly.eth/proposal/0xcf1ebeb8378bfcd92345b533bb35b4a3216260eade8d5368330da280598d8718

Quorum for community votes is 25%. So far, 18,440 (12%) are participating. If quorum is not reached, the motion to recapture PRIME will not be implemented.

Now that PRIME is unlocked and more tokens are in circulation, we may revisit the 25% quorum requirement to reflect more realistic participation targets. Any quorum changes would not take effect until after the current vote closes and would be subject to community discussion.

Also, please remember to vote in the Emissary Prime Election by 3/24/2023 9:00 AM. On March 27, we will announce official results. New EPs will be inaugurated on April 1.
https://snapshot.org/#/echelonassembly.eth/proposal/0x742166884c287f1f12feacc03bd2a9a6b1c97bfdfeb0afeddd2c7809799a129c

WORLDCOIN TEST@everyone this document provides updates on the ChainSafe grant proposal including a detailed breakdown of deliverables: https://docdro.id/LB6eccG 

Three main updates:
1) Marketplace fee share for ChainSafe changed from 50% to 25%. This represents 0.5%, instead of 1%, of the targeted 2% fee.
2) Marketplace fee for Chainsafe expires after 3 years.
3) Up to 40% of total cost, payable in PRIME, has been moved forward to December 2023. This cost is dollar-denominated – the corresponding PRIME amount is determined by market price at the time of transfer.

PRIME holders can vote for or against the proposal in a community vote starting 5/31/2023 9:00 AM. Votes will be shielded (hidden) on Snapshot until voting concludes 6/7/2023 9:00 AM.

Please keep related discussions in the #deleted-channel channel.
